    "instruction": "Load metric.csv, trace.csv, log.csv, and error_logs.csv. For each file return a compact summary (as a JSON/dict): {file_name, total_rows, min_timestamp, max_timestamp, unique_cmdb_ids (list up to 20), unique_kpi_or_trace_or_log_names (list up to 20) — for error_logs.csv return unique messages sample (up to 20) instead of KPI names}. Do not print full tables. Keep outputs strictly bounded as described."
}

{
    "analysis": "From the prior summaries: metric, trace and error log volumes concentrate on frontend pods (frontend-2, frontend-0, frontend-1). Traces show heavy activity originating from frontend pods and interacting with checkoutservice and productcatalogservice. Error logs are dominated by frontend pods and show repeated warning messages like 'failed to retrieve...'. Following the workflow, the next concrete preprocessing action is to enumerate the exact metric KPIs available for the top candidate components (so we can compute global thresholds for relevant KPIs). We should start with the frontend pods and a few downstream services shown in traces (checkoutservice and productcatalogservice) to limit scope.",
